Ad Text:
12 + 12 + 12 month contract - July start
NV1 Security Clearance required
5+ years in digital environment (Fed Gov) 
Sydney CBD address 

Our client, a large Australian Federal Government financial intelligence agency, require the services of a Senior Systems Analyst.

Duties of the Senior Systems Analyst

Translating business needs into detailed technical specifications & system designs;
Designing API request & response structures to enable seamless system integration & authoring technical specifications for APIs;
Conducting impact assessments across multiple systems & applications, presenting solution options, & recommending optimal approaches to stakeholders;
Collaborating with business stakeholders & technical leads to design & deliver fit-for-purpose solutions that align with organisational goals, standards, & compliance requirements;
Analysing, defining & documenting data mapping, transformation & enrichment rules; &
Producing comprehensive technical documentation of systems & data holdings.

Skills and Experience required

Minimum of 5 years’ experience in a digital environment, preferably within government (Federal);
Demonstrated passion for analysing complex system & business processes, translating requirements into technical specifications, & collaborating with cross-functional teams.
Experience in gathering and analysing system & business requirements, translating them into technical specifications;
Demonstrated ability in translating system and business problems into customer solutions;
Experience in managing end-user workshops, & in eliciting, documenting, & analysing requirements (desired);
Proficiency in Microsoft 365 tools & Atlassian products such as Confluence and JIRA (desired).

How to Apply 
